71
00:02:54,399 --> 00:02:56,839
and we are to be ambassadors.

72
00:02:56,839 --> 00:02:59,000
And what a blessing to be the representative

73
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:02,320
of the Lord Jesus Christ and to go and tell others.

74
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:05,039
We begin the sixth chapter and we find

75
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:09,960
that God says that we are workers together with him.

76
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,800
Of course, we understand that the verbiage

77
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,960
in the book of 1 Corinthians is used

78
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:16,320
that we are co-laborers, we're workers together,

79
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:17,919
co-laborers with Christ.

80
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:20,119
And what a blessing to think about the fact

81
00:03:20,119 --> 00:03:22,880
that we are workers together with God.

82
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:25,199
And the apostle Paul is seeking to encourage

83
00:03:25,199 --> 00:03:28,119
the believers in Corinth, he's trying to help them

84
00:03:28,119 --> 00:03:31,160
understand what their duty and responsibility

85
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:34,399
and privilege is and how they're to be engaged

86
00:03:34,399 --> 00:03:36,440
in the work of the ministry.

87
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:39,119
We find that as we come to the end of chapter number six

88
00:03:39,119 --> 00:03:42,080
in 2 Corinthians that these verses of scripture

89
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:44,639
are quite familiar and I would say it this way,

90
00:03:44,639 --> 00:03:47,679
oftentimes they are partially quoted.

91
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:50,039
We look at this portion of scripture

92
00:03:50,039 --> 00:03:53,919
and we find that the subject of biblical separation

93
00:03:53,919 --> 00:03:56,320
is addressed and it's absolutely imperative

94
00:03:56,320 --> 00:03:58,160
that we understand this morning

95
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:00,759
the importance of separation.

96
00:04:00,759 --> 00:04:04,160
I've titled the message simply that, biblical separation,

97
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:06,919
and we look at the Bible and we understand

98
00:04:06,919 --> 00:04:09,960
that there's the truth of ecclesiastical separation,

99
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:13,000
but there's also the truth of personal separation.

100
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,320
As we look through the passage of scripture this morning,

101
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:17,760
we are reminded of the Old Testament principle

102
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:20,359
that God gives us in the little prophet of Amos,

103
00:04:20,359 --> 00:04:22,239
chapter three and verse number three,

104
00:04:22,239 --> 00:04:27,239
can two walk together except they be agreed.

105
00:04:27,679 --> 00:04:30,000
And we find as we begin to look at this passage

106
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:32,320
of scripture, the apostle Paul is going to give

107
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:35,640
some very important truth to these believers

108
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:38,619
and God has chosen to preserve it for us today

109
00:04:38,619 --> 00:04:41,000
so that it would be to our benefit as well.

110
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,600
Begin reading with me in verse number 11,

111
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:45,279
the Bible says, O ye Corinthians,

112
00:04:45,279 --> 00:04:50,279
our mouth is open unto you, our heart is enlarged.

113
00:04:50,940 --> 00:04:52,399
You're not straightened in us,

114
00:04:52,399 --> 00:04:55,079
but ye are straightened in your own bowels.

115
00:04:55,079 --> 00:04:57,440
Now for a recompense in the same,

116
00:04:57,440 --> 00:05:00,880
I speak unto you as unto you my children,

117
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:03,679
be ye also enlarged.

118
00:05:03,679 --> 00:05:06,320
We'll go through chapter seven in verse one,

119
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:08,239
but let's dig right in this morning

120
00:05:08,239 --> 00:05:10,720
and I want you to notice just two points this morning.

121
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:12,239
The first thought is this,

122
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:14,799
I want you to notice with me in verses 11 through 13,

123
00:05:14,799 --> 00:05:17,799
Paul's care for the Corinthians.

124
00:05:17,799 --> 00:05:19,559
Paul's care for the Corinthians.

125
00:05:19,559 --> 00:05:21,679
We find that in these three verses of scripture

126
00:05:21,679 --> 00:05:23,320
that I've just read this morning,

127
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:27,519
that Paul is seeking to express his care and concern

128
00:05:27,519 --> 00:05:30,679
for these believers in the church of Corinth.

129
00:05:30,679 --> 00:05:32,200
We find that the apostle Paul,

130
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,839
you remember that there were some

131
00:05:33,839 --> 00:05:36,320
that were within the congregation of this church

132
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:39,399
that had been attacking the apostle Paul

133
00:05:39,399 --> 00:05:42,160
and their fellowship had been strained.

134
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,679
Remember they were saying that Paul says one thing,

135
00:05:44,679 --> 00:05:46,359
but he actually means something else

136
00:05:46,359 --> 00:05:48,799
and they're having all of this conflict

137
00:05:48,799 --> 00:05:50,279
with the apostle Paul.

138
00:05:50,279 --> 00:05:52,959
And so Paul in these verses of scripture,

139
00:05:52,959 --> 00:05:56,559
he's seeking to express to these believers

140
00:05:56,559 --> 00:05:59,519
how much he cares and loves them.

141
00:05:59,519 --> 00:06:01,880
We find that the apostle Paul,

142
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:04,880
he had when he understood the misunderstanding

143
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:08,119
as we read in chapter two and entering into chapter three

144
00:06:08,119 --> 00:06:10,320
of the book of second Corinthians,

145
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:11,279
that what did he do?

146
00:06:11,279 --> 00:06:15,320
Well, before he answered them and explained,

147
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:17,200
he first examined his own heart.

148
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,920
And as he examined his own heart

149
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:21,559
and took that process of self-examination,

150
00:06:21,559 --> 00:06:24,279
he then explained to the believers in Corinth

151
00:06:24,279 --> 00:06:26,799
that were saying things that were not true.

152
00:06:26,799 --> 00:06:29,279
And he explained to them why seeking

153
00:06:29,279 --> 00:06:32,600
to have some restoration in that fellowship.

154
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:35,799
Paul had labored amongst these believers.

155
00:06:35,799 --> 00:06:38,519
Paul had a heart for these believers.

156
00:06:38,559 --> 00:06:42,679
He loved them and he cared deeply for them.

157
00:06:42,679 --> 00:06:46,000
And so Paul is seeking to express this to them.

158
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:49,559
I believe that here is Paul would express to them

159
00:06:49,559 --> 00:06:50,640
in these few verses,

160
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:53,519
it reminds us as he gives even further truth

161
00:06:53,519 --> 00:06:55,480
in chapter 12, hold your place here,

162
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:57,359
but look at second Corinthians chapter 12

163
00:06:57,359 --> 00:06:59,679
and notice how the apostle Paul writes it

164
00:06:59,679 --> 00:07:02,359
here in these verses of scripture.

165
00:07:03,839 --> 00:07:07,720
The apostle Paul, because of this group in Corinth

166
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:10,519
that had opposed him and the relationship,

167
00:07:10,519 --> 00:07:12,040
the fellowship was strained,

168
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:15,799
I believe that their attitude and their spirit

169
00:07:15,799 --> 00:07:18,320
laid heavy upon his heart.

170
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:21,239
It was something that was greatly concerned about.

171
00:07:21,239 --> 00:07:23,519
And we find that in the 12th chapter,

172
00:07:23,519 --> 00:07:25,320
notice with me in verse number 14,

173
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:27,279
the Bible says, behold,

174
00:07:27,279 --> 00:07:30,279
the third time I am ready to come to you

175
00:07:30,279 --> 00:07:33,119
and I will not be burdensome to you.

176
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:34,160
Notice when he says,

177
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:38,279
for I seek not yours, but you.

178
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:41,920
For the children ought not to lay up for the parents,

179
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:44,720
but the parents for the children.

180
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:49,040
And I will very gladly spend and be spent.

181
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:51,880
Notice where he says for you,

182
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:55,399
though the more abundantly I love you,

183
00:07:55,399 --> 00:07:58,799
the less I be loved.

184
00:07:58,799 --> 00:08:01,000
The apostle Paul cared about these believers.

185
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,920
Why did he care so much about them?

186
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:05,559
Well, he knew that God had entrusted him

187
00:08:05,559 --> 00:08:09,559
with a responsibility to minister to them spiritually,

188
00:08:09,559 --> 00:08:11,959
to be a spiritual leader in their lives.

189
00:08:11,959 --> 00:08:15,679
And he knew that they one day would stand

190
00:08:15,679 --> 00:08:17,519
before the Lord Jesus Christ.

191
00:08:17,519 --> 00:08:20,600
And he desired that on that day,

192
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:24,399
they would be able to stand before Christ complete.

193
00:08:24,399 --> 00:08:28,559
That he had that desire, that longing for these,

194
00:08:28,559 --> 00:08:31,920
that God had given him the privilege of ministering to.

195
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:34,559
And what was happening is because of this conflict,

196
00:08:34,559 --> 00:08:36,559
because of their own attitude,

197
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:40,919
we find that they were resisting the message

198
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:45,119
that God had given Paul to deliver to them.

199
00:08:45,119 --> 00:08:47,359
Paul understood that it was God's word.

200
00:08:47,359 --> 00:08:50,840
Paul understood that it was profitable for those believers.

201
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:54,200
Paul understood that what God had given him,

202
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:58,640
these people needed, but they weren't gonna receive it

203
00:08:58,640 --> 00:09:01,780
because they had angst against Paul.

204
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:03,479
So what's Paul doing?

205
00:09:03,479 --> 00:09:05,299
Well, before he's gonna give them the great truth

206
00:09:05,299 --> 00:09:07,500
that we're gonna look at here in just a few moments,

207
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:11,700
he first lets them know how much he cares about them,

208
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:13,460
how much he loves them.

209
00:09:13,460 --> 00:09:16,020
We find that in Galatians chapter four,

210
00:09:16,020 --> 00:09:18,739
not concerning this particular church, obviously,

211
00:09:18,739 --> 00:09:21,619
but the Bible tells us in Galatians four,

212
00:09:21,619 --> 00:09:24,700
as Paul is writing back to those churches

213
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:26,580
in the region of Galatia, he says,

214
00:09:26,580 --> 00:09:28,900
"'Am I therefore become your enemy

215
00:09:28,900 --> 00:09:32,020
"'because I tell you the truth?'

216
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:34,020
Paul understood the importance of truth.

217
00:09:34,020 --> 00:09:34,940
He had been entrusted.

218
00:09:34,940 --> 00:09:37,219
He understood that God's word is truth,

219
00:09:37,219 --> 00:09:40,179
and he faithfully preached the word of God,

220
00:09:40,179 --> 00:09:43,239
but yet he says, "'Have I become your enemy

221
00:09:43,239 --> 00:09:45,380
"'because I tell you the truth?'

222
00:09:45,380 --> 00:09:47,940
You know what's sad is that there are many people today

223
00:09:47,940 --> 00:09:49,580
that do not know the truth.

224
00:09:50,580 --> 00:09:52,739
You know what's even more burdensome

225
00:09:52,739 --> 00:09:53,700
is there's a number of people

226
00:09:53,700 --> 00:09:56,419
that don't want to know the truth.

227
00:09:57,260 --> 00:09:58,099
They're just willingly ignorant,

228
00:09:58,099 --> 00:09:59,979
as it says in 2 Peter chapter three.

229
00:09:59,979 --> 00:10:02,019
They just don't wanna know the truth.

230
00:10:02,019 --> 00:10:05,339
They wanna continue down the path that they're traveling,

231
00:10:05,339 --> 00:10:07,659
believing whatever it is that they're believing.

232
00:10:07,659 --> 00:10:10,739
We have in our society today groups of people

233
00:10:10,739 --> 00:10:13,439
that will say, well, this is my truth and your truth

234
00:10:13,439 --> 00:10:14,419
and so on and so forth.

235
00:10:14,419 --> 00:10:17,359
The reality is that truth is not subjective.

236
00:10:17,359 --> 00:10:21,079
Truth is founded upon the Lord Jesus Christ and his word.

237
00:10:21,079 --> 00:10:23,099
And Paul says, if I'm giving you the truth,

238
00:10:23,099 --> 00:10:25,859
why are you treating me like I'm an enemy?

239
00:10:25,859 --> 00:10:26,899
What was Paul trying to do?

240
00:10:26,899 --> 00:10:29,459
He's trying to give them the truth to help them.

241
00:10:29,459 --> 00:10:30,859
You ever have somebody get upset with you

242
00:10:30,859 --> 00:10:32,459
because you give them the truth?

243
00:10:33,539 --> 00:10:36,599
The gospel's offensive, amen?

244
00:10:36,599 --> 00:10:38,599
And Lauren, I don't know where Lauren is,

245
00:10:38,599 --> 00:10:39,439
oh, there she is.

246
00:10:39,439 --> 00:10:40,859
You asked me a question a few weeks ago

247
00:10:40,859 --> 00:10:42,599
about people being upset about door knocking,

248
00:10:42,599 --> 00:10:44,779
and since then, I've gotten some calls.

249
00:10:44,779 --> 00:10:45,899
I'm not saying it's your fault,

250
00:10:45,899 --> 00:10:48,219
but man, we got a phone call where in Belgium,

251
00:10:48,219 --> 00:10:51,979
somebody just absolutely ripped us.

252
00:10:51,979 --> 00:10:53,699
I mean, just the profanity

253
00:10:53,699 --> 00:10:55,779
and just a short little voice message

254
00:10:55,779 --> 00:10:57,779
that was left on the voicemail at church

255
00:10:57,779 --> 00:11:00,779
about the fact that we left some gospel literature

256
00:11:00,779 --> 00:11:02,219
on their door.

257
00:11:02,219 --> 00:11:03,519
They don't want the truth.

258
00:11:04,699 --> 00:11:08,139
You know, I wasn't mad about the voicemail.

259
00:11:08,139 --> 00:11:09,459
My heart was saddened.

260
00:11:10,659 --> 00:11:12,979
Because that individual identified themselves

261
00:11:12,979 --> 00:11:17,979
on that phone call as being a proud pagan atheist.

262
00:11:20,579 --> 00:11:22,139
That's how they described themselves.

263
00:11:22,139 --> 00:11:24,539
And here's the immediate thought that I had.

264
00:11:24,539 --> 00:11:28,859
They held in their hand the very truth

265
00:11:31,439 --> 00:11:33,419
that would save their soul.

266
00:11:34,979 --> 00:11:36,019
And they rejected it.

267
00:11:37,219 --> 00:11:40,939
And they got mad about the truth.

268
00:11:40,939 --> 00:11:41,779
It's nothing new.

269
00:11:41,779 --> 00:11:44,259
Paul experienced this, but Paul's trying to convey

270
00:11:44,259 --> 00:11:46,859
and to communicate to the believers in Corinth,

271
00:11:46,859 --> 00:11:50,339
I love you, I'm trying to help you.

272
00:11:50,339 --> 00:11:52,879
You ever see children that don't like the instruction

273
00:11:52,879 --> 00:11:54,119
that a parent gives?

274
00:11:54,119 --> 00:11:56,319
And they're rebellious against the instruction

275
00:11:56,319 --> 00:11:57,279
that the parent gives, why?

276
00:11:57,279 --> 00:11:59,599
Because they want what they want.

277
00:11:59,599 --> 00:12:03,079
And they believe that what they want will satisfy them.

278
00:12:03,079 --> 00:12:05,119
And the parent knows better.

279
00:12:05,119 --> 00:12:08,639
And there's great difficulty oftentimes that occurs.

280
00:12:08,639 --> 00:12:10,999
And the reality is that we understand

281
00:12:10,999 --> 00:12:14,079
that here the Apostle Paul, he says,

282
00:12:14,079 --> 00:12:17,239
I wanna give you something that's good for you.

283
00:12:20,359 --> 00:12:22,839
In First Thessalonians chapter number two,

284
00:12:23,679 --> 00:12:25,439
Paul mentions to the church in Thessalonica

285
00:12:25,439 --> 00:12:27,079
about his care for them.

286
00:12:27,079 --> 00:12:29,759
See, this is consistent in the life of Paul

287
00:12:29,759 --> 00:12:33,479
that he cared about those to whom God had given him

288
00:12:33,479 --> 00:12:35,799
the opportunity to minister.

289
00:12:35,799 --> 00:12:37,559
We find that in verse number seven

290
00:12:37,559 --> 00:12:39,759
of First Thessalonians chapter two,

291
00:12:39,759 --> 00:12:43,339
notice what Paul says, but we were gentle among you.

292
00:12:44,239 --> 00:12:47,599
Even as a nurse cherisheth her children,

293
00:12:47,599 --> 00:12:51,279
so being affectionately desirous of you,

294
00:12:51,279 --> 00:12:53,479
we were willing to have imparted unto you

295
00:12:53,479 --> 00:12:57,199
not the gospel of God only, but also our own souls,

296
00:12:57,199 --> 00:13:01,559
because ye were dear unto us.

297
00:13:01,559 --> 00:13:03,399
The reality this morning is that Paul,

298
00:13:03,399 --> 00:13:05,679
notice what he says in verse number 11 back in our text.

299
00:13:05,679 --> 00:13:09,119
He says, oh, ye Corinthians, notice he says,

300
00:13:09,119 --> 00:13:12,459
our mouth is open unto you.

301
00:13:12,459 --> 00:13:15,279
Paul believed because he understood the work

302
00:13:15,279 --> 00:13:16,739
that God had entrusted him with.

303
00:13:16,739 --> 00:13:20,439
Listen, Paul knew his position as being an Apostle.

304
00:13:20,439 --> 00:13:22,159
Paul knew his calling.

305
00:13:22,159 --> 00:13:25,919
He knew that God had called him to be a preacher

306
00:13:25,919 --> 00:13:28,359
of the gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ.

307
00:13:28,359 --> 00:13:31,959
God had made it clear, and Paul clearly communicates

308
00:13:31,959 --> 00:13:34,359
throughout the epistles that he knew

309
00:13:34,359 --> 00:13:36,999
that he was doing the work of God.

310
00:13:38,719 --> 00:13:40,359
He says, I'm warning you, why?

311
00:13:40,359 --> 00:13:44,279
To present you perfect or complete at that day.

312
00:13:44,279 --> 00:13:47,119
He says that to the people in Colossae

313
00:13:47,119 --> 00:13:50,239
in Colossians chapter one, and we find that Paul knew,

314
00:13:51,079 --> 00:13:52,359
and he says, our mouth is open unto you.

315
00:13:52,359 --> 00:13:57,359
He continues in verse 11 and says, our heart is enlarged.

316
00:13:57,779 --> 00:14:00,439
Paul says, listen, I'm not mad at you.

317
00:14:00,439 --> 00:14:03,319
I'm not, there's no, it's not on my side.

318
00:14:03,319 --> 00:14:06,079
You're resisting me, and I want you to know

319
00:14:06,079 --> 00:14:07,959
that my mouth is open to you,

320
00:14:07,959 --> 00:14:11,039
that my heart is enlarged unto you,

321
00:14:11,039 --> 00:14:13,799
and we find that then in verses 12 and 13,

322
00:14:13,799 --> 00:14:15,879
what Paul was communicating, he says,

323
00:14:15,879 --> 00:14:17,539
ye are not straightened in us.

324
00:14:17,539 --> 00:14:20,139
Again, it's not the fact that I have something

325
00:14:20,959 --> 00:14:24,019
against you, but ye are straightened in your own bowels,

326
00:14:24,019 --> 00:14:25,979
not for a recompense in the same.

327
00:14:25,979 --> 00:14:28,819
I speak as unto my children.

328
00:14:28,819 --> 00:14:31,019
Be ye also enlarged.

329
00:14:31,019 --> 00:14:32,059
What is he doing?

330
00:14:32,059 --> 00:14:34,579
Paul is communicating to them, and he's desiring

331
00:14:34,579 --> 00:14:36,339
that their fellowship be restored.

332
00:14:36,339 --> 00:14:38,619
He's literally pleading with them.

333
00:14:38,619 --> 00:14:41,659
He loves them, and he desires to minister to them,

334
00:14:41,659 --> 00:14:45,659
and he wants them to open their hearts to him

335
00:14:46,659 --> 00:14:50,579
because he knew that if their heart was closed to him,

336
00:14:50,579 --> 00:14:54,419
they weren't gonna receive what God had for them.

337
00:14:55,739 --> 00:14:58,259
I've had times over the years where I'd get a phone call

338
00:14:58,259 --> 00:15:01,579
from someone and say, hey, my neighbor or my relative,

339
00:15:01,579 --> 00:15:03,779
they need some help, would you go help them?

340
00:15:04,699 --> 00:15:06,859
And I say, nope, you can give them my phone number,

341
00:15:06,859 --> 00:15:09,459
and if they want help, they can call me.

342
00:15:09,459 --> 00:15:10,299
You know why I do that?

343
00:15:10,299 --> 00:15:12,499
Because I've learned that if I try to go help someone

344
00:15:12,499 --> 00:15:13,619
that doesn't really want help,

345
00:15:13,619 --> 00:15:16,499
it's just absolutely torturous for me.

346
00:15:19,139 --> 00:15:21,539
And the reality is that Paul's saying,

347
00:15:21,539 --> 00:15:24,259
I have something that's beneficial for you.

348
00:15:24,259 --> 00:15:25,379
Why, because he's Paul?

349
00:15:25,379 --> 00:15:27,739
No, because it's God's word.

350
00:15:27,739 --> 00:15:29,459
He knows, he says all scripture is given

351
00:15:29,459 --> 00:15:33,699
by inspiration of God and is profitable.

352
00:15:33,699 --> 00:15:35,819
And so Paul says, I have this for you,

353
00:15:35,819 --> 00:15:38,139
and I want you to know how much I care for you

354
00:15:38,139 --> 00:15:40,139
and how much I love you.

355
00:15:40,139 --> 00:15:41,999
And a man asked me a number of years ago

356
00:15:41,999 --> 00:15:44,159
as I would share the gospel with him repeatedly

357
00:15:44,159 --> 00:15:46,159
and he would just continue to resist

358
00:15:46,159 --> 00:15:47,839
and to resist and to reject.

359
00:15:47,839 --> 00:15:51,239
And I find that eventually on one particular day,

360
00:15:51,239 --> 00:15:55,559
he looked straight in my face and he said, why do you care?

361
00:15:56,839 --> 00:15:58,039
It's what he said to me.

362
00:15:59,319 --> 00:16:01,799
He said this, he followed up the statement by saying,

363
00:16:01,799 --> 00:16:05,399
why do you care by saying, so what if I go to hell?

364
00:16:06,239 --> 00:16:07,479
It's what he said to me.

365
00:16:07,479 --> 00:16:09,879
I couldn't imagine the words that I was hearing.

366
00:16:10,799 --> 00:16:14,519
And he said, but why do you care if I don't even care?

367
00:16:14,519 --> 00:16:15,399
It's what he said.

368
00:16:16,559 --> 00:16:18,359
You know what I told him?

369
00:16:18,359 --> 00:16:19,839
I said, I understand the truth of God's word

370
00:16:19,839 --> 00:16:21,359
and I believe it.

371
00:16:21,359 --> 00:16:23,239
You're gonna die one day.

372
00:16:23,239 --> 00:16:25,399
You're gonna go to heaven or hell.

373
00:16:25,399 --> 00:16:28,519
God loves you and he wants you to be saved.

374
00:16:28,519 --> 00:16:29,639
He died for you.

375
00:16:30,879 --> 00:16:32,239
And here's what I told this individual.

376
00:16:32,239 --> 00:16:34,439
I said, listen, I'm going to heaven

377
00:16:34,439 --> 00:16:35,959
whether you get saved or not.

378
00:16:36,919 --> 00:16:39,159
It's not necessarily a benefit.

379
00:16:39,159 --> 00:16:40,879
It's not like it helps me get to heaven

380
00:16:40,879 --> 00:16:44,439
because no, I want you to go to heaven with me.

381
00:16:45,639 --> 00:16:47,679
But I'm going to heaven whether you receive

382
00:16:47,679 --> 00:16:49,919
or reject the truth of the gospel.

383
00:16:49,919 --> 00:16:52,159
And the reality is that Paul, listen,

384
00:16:52,159 --> 00:16:54,439
he understood his walk with God.

385
00:16:54,439 --> 00:16:57,079
Paul understood, he talks about at the end

386
00:16:57,079 --> 00:16:59,279
of the book of Second Timothy that he's finished,

387
00:16:59,279 --> 00:17:01,359
he's completed, he's done the work

388
00:17:01,359 --> 00:17:02,519
that God's called him to do.

389
00:17:02,519 --> 00:17:04,679
He knew that there would be a crown for him.

390
00:17:04,679 --> 00:17:07,279
He knew that he had, not that he's perfect,

391
00:17:07,279 --> 00:17:10,959
but he was seeking to do what God had called him to do.

392
00:17:10,959 --> 00:17:13,319
He said that he exercised himself

393
00:17:13,319 --> 00:17:16,119
to have always a conscience void of offense

394
00:17:16,119 --> 00:17:17,919
before God and man.

395
00:17:17,919 --> 00:17:20,759
And so Paul was seeking to walk with God,

396
00:17:20,759 --> 00:17:24,199
but he wanted others to benefit from the truth

397
00:17:24,199 --> 00:17:26,159
that God had given him.

398
00:17:26,159 --> 00:17:27,239
So what does he do?

399
00:17:27,239 --> 00:17:31,079
He expresses his care, his love, his concern.

400
00:17:32,239 --> 00:17:33,839
It's not a Bible verse.

401
00:17:33,879 --> 00:17:36,999
It's not a Bible verse, but I believe it is a principle

402
00:17:36,999 --> 00:17:40,759
that is certainly founded upon biblical truth,

403
00:17:40,759 --> 00:17:41,599
and that is this.

404
00:17:41,599 --> 00:17:44,519
Many times people don't care how much you know

405
00:17:44,519 --> 00:17:47,039
until they know how much you care.

406
00:17:47,039 --> 00:17:49,279
And we've used that phrase at times,

407
00:17:49,279 --> 00:17:52,679
and we understand that, again, it's not a Bible verse,

408
00:17:52,679 --> 00:17:55,039
but I believe the concept and the thought

409
00:17:55,039 --> 00:17:58,479
is certainly founded upon biblical principle.

410
00:17:59,359 --> 00:18:03,879
This morning before Paul gets into the subject of separation

411
00:18:03,879 --> 00:18:06,759
we find that he expresses his care

412
00:18:06,759 --> 00:18:09,399
to these believers in Corinth.

413
00:18:09,399 --> 00:18:10,999
I wonder this morning,

414
00:18:10,999 --> 00:18:13,879
how many people truly know that we care about them,

415
00:18:13,879 --> 00:18:15,479
that we love them?

416
00:18:15,479 --> 00:18:17,719
You know, people have all kinds of ideas

417
00:18:17,719 --> 00:18:21,199
about church and religion, quote unquote.

418
00:18:21,199 --> 00:18:24,679
They think that somehow you're going to benefit

419
00:18:24,679 --> 00:18:25,759
or I'm going to benefit,

420
00:18:25,759 --> 00:18:28,119
that we're trying to get some gain for ourselves,

421
00:18:28,759 --> 00:18:30,959
but the reality is that we're simply seeking

422
00:18:30,959 --> 00:18:34,959
to impart truth to someone that will benefit them.

423
00:18:36,119 --> 00:18:38,159
Now, do we seek to teach them all things

424
00:18:38,159 --> 00:18:39,440
whatsoever I've commanded you?

425
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:42,159
Yes, we do seek to disciple and to train

426
00:18:42,159 --> 00:18:44,479
and to teach the truth of God's word.

427
00:18:44,479 --> 00:18:45,320
Why?

428
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:47,359
Because it's God's plan that all of God's people

429
00:18:47,359 --> 00:18:48,719
are conformed to the image of Christ,

430
00:18:48,719 --> 00:18:51,119
and you're going to stand before Christ one day.

431
00:18:51,959 --> 00:18:53,239
But Paul says, I love you.

432
00:18:53,239 --> 00:18:55,959
My heart's, my mouth is open unto you.

433
00:18:56,839 --> 00:18:59,119
Our heart is enlarged.

434
00:18:59,119 --> 00:19:00,079
So what does he say?

435
00:19:00,079 --> 00:19:02,079
Be ye also enlarged.

436
00:19:03,760 --> 00:19:06,119
We find that Paul's care for the Corinthians

437
00:19:06,119 --> 00:19:08,119
is revealed in verses 11 through 13.

438
00:19:08,119 --> 00:19:09,839
As we look at the remainder of the text

439
00:19:09,839 --> 00:19:11,559
and enter into the seventh chapter,

440
00:19:11,559 --> 00:19:16,159
we find number two, Paul's counsel to the Corinthians.

441
00:19:16,159 --> 00:19:17,679
Paul's counsel to the Corinthians.

442
00:19:17,679 --> 00:19:22,119
By the way, counsel is regularly received far better

443
00:19:22,119 --> 00:19:24,440
from someone or by someone

444
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:26,279
that knows that you care about them.

445
00:19:27,359 --> 00:19:29,159
So you care about them.

446
00:19:29,159 --> 00:19:30,760
He says this in verse 14,

447
00:19:30,760 --> 00:19:34,799
be ye not unequally yoked together with unbelievers.

448
00:19:34,799 --> 00:19:37,440
For what fellowship hath righteousness with unrighteousness

449
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:40,359
and what communion hath light with darkness?

450
00:19:40,359 --> 00:19:43,239
And what concord hath Christ with Belial

451
00:19:43,239 --> 00:19:47,399
or what part hath he that believeth with an infidel?

452
00:19:47,399 --> 00:19:51,320
And what agreement hath the temple of God with idols?

453
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:54,079
For ye are the temple of the living God

454
00:19:54,719 --> 00:19:57,320
and as God hath said, I will dwell in them and walk in them

455
00:19:57,320 --> 00:20:00,320
and I will be their God and they shall be mine.

456
00:20:00,320 --> 00:20:03,460
My people, wherefore, come out from among them,

457
00:20:03,460 --> 00:20:06,220
and be ye separate, saith the Lord,

458
00:20:06,220 --> 00:20:08,360
and touch not the unclean thing,

459
00:20:08,360 --> 00:20:11,160
and I will receive you and will be a father unto you,

460
00:20:11,160 --> 00:20:13,140
and you shall be my sons and daughters,

461
00:20:13,140 --> 00:20:14,700
saith the Lord Almighty,

462
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:18,600
having therefore these promises, dearly beloved.

463
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:20,880
Let us cleanse ourselves from all filthiness

464
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:22,400
of the flesh and spirit,

465
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:26,440
perfecting holiness in the fear of God.

466
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:28,840
What great counsel that we read

467
00:20:28,840 --> 00:20:30,600
in these verses of scripture.

468
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:33,680
And we find that the counsel is really given

469
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:37,240
to us in verse 14, and then again, repeated in verse 17.

470
00:20:37,240 --> 00:20:38,580
And here's the counsel,

471
00:20:38,580 --> 00:20:43,580
be ye not unequally yoked together with unbelievers.

472
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:47,480
He rephrases it and says it this way in verse 17,

473
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:50,220
wherefore, come out from among them,

474
00:20:50,220 --> 00:20:54,040
and be ye separate, saith the Lord,

475
00:20:54,040 --> 00:20:55,700
and touch not the unclean thing,

476
00:20:55,700 --> 00:20:57,760
and I will receive you.

477
00:20:57,760 --> 00:21:01,120
We find that the counsel is very straightforward.

478
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:05,260
Be not unequally yoked together with unbelievers.

479
00:21:05,260 --> 00:21:07,200
It's very straightforward, it's simple.

480
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:12,500
Then Paul spends the next couple of verses of scripture

481
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:14,900
in providing examples

482
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:17,780
as he explains this truth of separation.

483
00:21:17,780 --> 00:21:19,980
Notice the explanation that is given

484
00:21:19,980 --> 00:21:23,140
beginning in verse 14 and really down through verse 16.

485
00:21:23,140 --> 00:21:25,480
In verse 14, the counsel had been given,

486
00:21:25,500 --> 00:21:28,080
be not unequally yoked together with unbelievers,

487
00:21:28,080 --> 00:21:29,780
but then we find the explanation.

488
00:21:29,780 --> 00:21:31,080
Notice he says this,

489
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:35,020
and he explains it by asking a series of questions.

490
00:21:35,020 --> 00:21:39,080
The questions that he asks are actually very easy to answer.

491
00:21:39,080 --> 00:21:42,360
Notice he says the first one in verse 14,

492
00:21:42,360 --> 00:21:46,900
he says, for what fellowship hath righteousness

493
00:21:46,900 --> 00:21:49,000
with unrighteousness?

494
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:50,560
The things that are right

495
00:21:50,560 --> 00:21:51,760
and the things that are not right.

496
00:21:51,760 --> 00:21:55,100
What fellowship do they have one with the other?

497
00:21:55,760 --> 00:21:58,560
It's pretty obvious as Paul is seeking to explain

498
00:21:58,560 --> 00:22:00,260
the counsel that he's just given

499
00:22:00,260 --> 00:22:02,020
to these believers in Corinth,

500
00:22:02,020 --> 00:22:03,940
and he begins to ask them these questions.

501
00:22:03,940 --> 00:22:06,600
What's the purpose of asking the question?

502
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,600
Is the purpose of asking the question

503
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:12,080
for Paul to gain some knowledge or wisdom?

504
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:16,080
See, sometimes we ask questions for information, right?

505
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:19,240
I don't know something, so I ask someone a question

506
00:22:19,240 --> 00:22:23,560
so that I can gain information because I am not aware.

507
00:22:23,620 --> 00:22:27,220
The questions that are asked here are not for information.

508
00:22:27,220 --> 00:22:28,680
You ever hear somebody use the phrase

509
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:32,360
that that's a thought-provoking question?

510
00:22:32,360 --> 00:22:36,320
Sometimes a question is asked so that the receiver,

511
00:22:36,320 --> 00:22:38,360
the recipient of that question,

512
00:22:38,360 --> 00:22:41,400
has a time of really considering

513
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:44,740
and contemplating in their own hearts and minds

514
00:22:44,740 --> 00:22:46,840
the truth that is being given.

515
00:22:47,740 --> 00:22:50,740
And here is the apostle Paul ask these questions

516
00:22:50,740 --> 00:22:52,340
to these believers in Corinth,

517
00:22:52,460 --> 00:22:55,020
and he says, what fellowship hath righteousness

518
00:22:55,020 --> 00:22:56,100
with unrighteousness?

519
00:22:56,100 --> 00:22:59,020
He's not really necessarily seeking information

520
00:22:59,020 --> 00:23:00,820
or expecting them to answer,

521
00:23:00,820 --> 00:23:04,480
but he's trying to communicate to them the truth

522
00:23:04,480 --> 00:23:07,820
that hey, why is the counsel to be separate?

523
00:23:07,820 --> 00:23:12,820
Why is the counsel to be not unequally yoked together

524
00:23:12,860 --> 00:23:13,700
